                     li Strategy                        li Process workflow research                        li User research                    ul                        li Development of ecosystem                        li Software application architecture                        li Quality assurance                    ul                        li Technical documentation                        li Third party security audit                        li Fully-functional product (go live)        .screen-background.lazy(data-src="/assets/images/cases/music-copyright/background-screen.jpg")            .container                h2 Background                p                    | Copyright management is one of the biggest pain points in the music industry. Every time we hear a song, the author is supposed to get paid. But it&apos;s impossible to track billions of cases when a music composition is played on the radio, at a club or bar without paying the performance rights organizations.                p                    | Digital monitoring doesn&apos;t help much to overcome piracy and lower both businesses&apos; and artists&apos; losses. Trials on unpaid royalties can last years because of difficulties in tracking where money was lost.        .screen-problems            .container                h2 Problems                section                    ul                        li                            | Current music copyright                            u system is outdated                            |  and stuck in bureaucracy                        li                            | Copyright infringements are                            u a global issue                        li                            | It&apos;s                            u hard to trace the ownership chain                            |  for copyrighted works                        li                            u Authors lose money                            |  on intermediaries who can&apos;t guarantee full rights protection                        li                            | Money flows in the industry are                            u unbelievably complicated and barely understood                            |  by most participants                        li                            | Authors                            u have to share their income with intermediaries                            |  without any reasonable justification                        li                            | Earning money from streaming music is accessible                            u only for top musicians                    article                        h4 All solved by one solution: Apla        .screen-representative            .container                .thumb.thumb-lg.mask.mask-white                    img(src='/assets/images/cases//music-copyright/rethink-logo.png' alt='')                h4                    | 20-50% of music payments don&apos;t make it to their rightful owners. Fair music: transparency and payment flows within the music industry                h5 Rethink Music                small Berklee Institute for Creative Entrepreneurship, July 2015        .screen-challenge            .container                h2 Challenge                section                    ul                        li                            | Create a blockchain-powered copyright protection system for music tracks.                        li                            | Allow authors and rights holders to receive direct revenues for every use of their work.                        li                            | Make license chain 100% transparent and traceable for the authors.                        li                            | Create the possibility for everyone to become a fairly paid author, skipping out intermediaries.                        li                            | Enable the option to buy the music directly from the authors via micro-payments.                        li                            | Introduce the solution to the wide audience as an interactive installation.        .screen-result.lazy(data-src="/assets/images/cases/music-copyright/result-screen.jpg")            .container                h5 Result                h4                    | An application for music copyright management integrated into an interactive installation &quot;The Spectrum&quot;        .screen-approach            .container                h2 Approach                .steps                    h5 Develop an ecosystem to meet the client&apos;s needs                    h5 Create a register for rights holders                    h5 Make a working prototype of the application                    h5 Proof-of-concept                .line                    h5 10 days                    h5 Validated by client        .screen-solution            .container                h2 Solution                section                    ol(type='1')                        li                            | The author uploads the sound recording to his private copyright storage.                        li                            | For every artwork, a unique copyright key is created, assigned to the music and saved permanently to the blockchain.                        li                            | The author can add the music to the digital Music Tracks Marketplace, setting the royalties to get a copy, to play it in public or the price to buy ownership.                    ol(start='4')                        li                            | The users choose music and make the desired purchases.                        li                            | The author can trace all the history of their copyright assignments anytime.                        li                            | The app allows to securely store the records and copyright data.                .img          